snippet.textDisplay:
Alright, I'm gonna have to bring out the Star Wars nerd in me here...
Force Healing: First exhibited in Ep4 where Obi Wan healed Luke after the sand people attacked him. Is also quite commonly used in Legends
Force Lightning: We saw Palpatine use it in Ep6, and while it's been surmised to be a dark side weapon, that's not confirmed in canon, and at that point, Rey WAS overwhelmed with emotion, the drive behind the Dark side, so I'll give that a pass.
Passing the lightsaber through their link: Honestly, I've got nothing there, it was something introduced in the last movie and what happened there is a rather logical extension, and was hinted throughout the movie, so...yeah.

Leia doing a Mary Poppins: Nothing more than a force pull, she's pulling the ship towards her, and since her mass is a LOT less than the ship, she was the one who moved. Not really a big problem.


At the end of the day, Star Wars is a series that isn't supposed to be all that serious. While some fantastic stories have been made (seriously, watch the Mandalorian), in both canon and legends (If you read, pick up Heir to the Empire, and fall in love with Mara Jade) that are great entertainment. But nitpicking the movies to death is not what Star Wars is about. Enjoy it for what it is, I actually was quite entertained by The Last Jedi, and Rise of Skywalker was a big middle finger to that movie, and I loved the Rise of Skywalker. Just nosh your popcorn and slurp your pop, and enjoy a couple of hours of good guys beating bad guys.
